I was on a time crunch waiting during a layover at the Amtrak train station. With no transportation, I decided to order for delivery. Was promised that the food would arrive in 30 mins, but it never arrived within the time frame. Called to see what was happening & was told they wouldn't be able to deliver before my train left. So, I waited 30 mins for food I would never get without being notified & had to board for a 2 and a half hour train ride on a completely empty stomach. Thanks Jimmy Johns.

Honestly, this Jimmy Johns is a good store, but the only good employee I've seen is Tyler Richards, I had an amazing talk with him and he deserves a promotion.  P.S: Food sucks, cookies are as hard as rock. 3 stars.
